<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=8174.topic&start=41&stop=49">pub102.ezboard.com/fthema...41&stop=49</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
LordGojirax was mentioning aggro issues he had in PoP, and while I'm not disputing that this can happen, I though I would related my experience with healing pets.<br>
<br>
Unless it's change in the past month, my cleric get zero aggro from healing my pet.  As a matter of fact, he doesn't even get a faction hit.<br>
<br>
I leveled up my cleric in Jagged Pines grouped with my mage.  I also used the opportunity to get faction for the Qeynos badge of Nobility.  Unless the cleric hit the mobs with a detrimental spell, or buffed/healed my mage when the mage had aggro, he didn't get a faction hit.  As well, I would stack multiple mobs (all KOS) on my pet, which is very &quot;loose&quot; aggro, and CH my pet and never get aggro.  If my mage tried to sit, the &quot;loose&quot; mobs would immediatly come over and bop him.  The cleric could sit down with impunity.  As long as he didn't get in melee range it was all good.<br>
<br>
I've also taken my cleric/mage to Lower Guk liveside, where the cleric is non-KOS, and used the heal pet strategy there.  I've pretty much sat on the Froglok King's lap healing my pet and gotten zero aggro.<br>
<br>
I also used the non-pet-aggro-healing to easily take out T'Serrina in ToFS.  No-Aggro == no getting summoned for healing.<br>
